Osun State Commissioner for Works and Transport, Remi Omowaiye has expressed optimism that the current rift between his boss and his predecessor in office, Ogbeni Rauf Aregbesola will soon be over. Omowaiye featuring on a Yoruba current affairs interview programme tagged, ‘Oro Oselu’, on Rave FM radio station, monitored in Osogbo, noted that rift of such do happen in politics but our leaders know how they settle such dispute in the party at the appropriate time. According to him, “rift do happen in politics but our leaders know how they settle the dispute in the party. Aregbesola is my brother and he is also my leader but sometimes we may have differences and later come together in politics. Olubadan: Oyetola Commiserates With Makinde, Oyo people Osun: Oyetola Signs 2022 Appropriation Bill Into Law “Osun state is not the first place that incumbent governors will have issues with their predecessors. It has been happening in different places before, some survive and others use elections to settle the matter between them. Omowaiye who also served as Commissioner under the Aregbesola led administration in the state hinted that he has been in politics before the arrival of Aregbesola in Osun. He claimed that his participation in active politics in the state is more than two decades, adding that the Minister for Interior, Rauf Aregbosola remains his political leader in Osun. According to him, “Mr. Rauf Aregbesola is our leader. Have been participating in politics since 2001 in the state before his arrival but Ogbeni is our leader and we will regard him as our leader always.